n range(i + 1, n):\n                for k in range(j + 1, n):\n                    if nums[i] != nums[j] and nums[i] != nums[k] and nums[j] != nums[k]:\n                        count += 1\n        return count\n```\n\nThis code iterates through all possible triplets (i, j, k) with the condition 0 <= i < j < k < nums.length and checks if the elements at these indices are pairwise distinct. If they are, it increments the count. Finally, it returns the count of such triplets.", "estimated_date": 1668902400000}